## Implementation Details

The Analytics component is placed at the end of the main App component's JSX return statement, which is the recommended location according to Vercel's documentation. This ensures that:

1. Analytics loads after the main application content
2. Page views and user interactions are tracked across all routes/states
3. The component doesn't block or interfere with the application's functionality

## Next Steps for Full Activation

To enable analytics data collection in production:

1. **Deploy to Vercel**: Push the code to Vercel (already configured)
2. **Enable in Dashboard**: Go to your Vercel project dashboard → Analytics tab
3. **Verify Tracking**: After deployment, check browser Network tab for requests to `/<unique-path>/view`

## Notes

- The implementation follows best practices from the official Vercel Analytics documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart)
- No additional configuration is needed for basic web analytics tracking
- Analytics will automatically track page views and Web Vitals metrics
- The component is tree-shakeable and won't impact bundle size if analytics is disabled

